<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>守护者</title><description>卫报全文RSS。获取更多全文RSS：https://feedx.net</description><link/> https://theguardian.com <item><title><![CDATA[Three dead in firefighting plane crash in outback Queensland]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/nov/05/queensland-outback-plane-crash-kills-aerial-firefighters-near-cloncurry]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T23:40:12Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7babc0daa2f55a9bf8a7d0a7b614d0da8a4e19f9/0_130_4000_2401 /master/4000.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=db2e2b3b780588142a90516c376d2998&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;警察胶带的通用图像&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;空中消防队的三名成员在轻型飞机在昆士兰州西北部偏远地区坠毁。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周六下午 2.30 左右，一名公众发出警报，报告坠机事故发生在克朗克里附近麦金利西北部的一个矿场附近。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; >; &lt;p>;警方表示，救援直升机机组人员发现了残骸，警察于下午 5 点左右抵达现场，确认机上三人全部死亡。&lt;/p>; &lt;ul>; &lt;li>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;&lt;a href= &quot;https://www.theguardian.com/email-newsletters?CMP=copyembed&quot;>;注册澳大利亚卫报免费的上午和下午电子邮件通讯，获取每日新闻摘要&lt;/a>;&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>;&lt;/ li>; &lt;/ul>; &lt;p>;昆士兰消防和紧急服务中心 (QFES) 表示，飞机坠毁时正在从图文巴飞往伊萨山的途中进行线路扫描。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-canonical-url =&quot;https://twitter.com/QldFES/status/1720736306559697314&quot;>; &lt;blockquote>; &lt;p>;今天下午在昆士兰州西北部发生致命的飞机失事以及三名支持我们丛林大火应对行动的人员悲惨丧生，我们的心情十分沉重。在昆士兰发生自然灾害时，我们作为一个家庭做出反应。这个家庭包括那些签约支持我们的……&lt;/p>;—昆士兰消防与消防局。紧急情况 (@QldFES) &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/QldFES/status/1720736306559697314?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;2023 年 11 月 4 日&lt;/a>; &lt;/blockquote>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;昆士兰州州长 Annastacia Palaszczuk 以及消防和紧急服务部长 Mark Ryan 于周六晚上发表声明，向船员的家人、朋友和同事表示同情。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;三人当时正在玩耍他们说，他们通过空中情报和测绘工作来帮助地面消防员，在拯救生命和保护财产方面发挥着关键作用。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我对所发生的事情感到非常悲伤，”Palaszczuk 说。&lt; /p>; &lt;p>;“这架飞机上的机组人员一直在竭尽全力保护昆士兰人。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我向受到这一令人震惊事件影响的许多人表示衷心的哀悼。” &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;瑞安表示，这场悲剧将对空中消防队造成沉重打击。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“他们很多人互相认识，共同努力，致力于同一个目标，确保每个人的安全， ”他说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;QFES 还向船员家属表示哀悼。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“此时此刻，我们的思念和祈祷与他们的家人同在，”它在一份声明中表示。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;QFES 表示，坠毁的飞机与用于扑灭丛林大火的大型空中加油机 (LAT) 的主机型号相同。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“ LAT 和主机将停飞，直至当局提出建议。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;总理安东尼·艾博尼斯 (Anthony Albanese) 赞扬了消防员的勇敢。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“所有澳大利亚人都心系家人、朋友、以及所有认识在昆士兰州北部发生的致命空难中丧生的勇敢消防员的人，”他周六晚上在访问中国时说道。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们知道阿尔巴尼斯说：“那些扑灭火灾、挺身而出的紧急服务人员，每天冒着生命危险，帮助澳大利亚同胞和社区。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“今天，我们的心与大家同在。” ”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;澳大利亚运输和安全局表示，来自布里斯班的调查小组正准备前往事故现场。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;初步报告预计将在大约六到八周内发布。 ATSB 表示。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;昆士兰警方也在调查，并将为验尸官准备一份报告。&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href =&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 05 Nov 2023 09:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Murder charge after human bones found in burnt-out tree trunk in NSW]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/nov/05/charge-after-human-bones-found-in-burnt-out-tree-trunk-in-nsw]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-05T01:13:27Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/1c02aa02fea5b65983393d1b4ecccecdeef16705/0_202_2332_1399 /master/2332.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=2929bb345dbf89d1de65bc175ae0e19b&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;David Collisson&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;在烧毁的树干中发现人类遗骸导致对一名在监狱里待了二十年的失踪男子提出谋杀指控。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周六，警方在 Maroubra 警察局逮捕了一名 33 岁男子，并指控其谋杀 David Collisson。&lt;/p>; &lt; p>;53 岁的 Collisson 于 10 月 15 日被报告失踪，最后一次出现在新南威尔士州马奇西北梅纳的一处房产。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他出狱二十多年后就神秘失踪了。在他被判对 17 岁的 Shahab Kargarian 进行“冷血、无情和残忍的枪杀”后。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Shahab 和他 17 岁的女友 Shabnam Faiz 在悉尼北部的一个公园里吃外卖。 2000 年，科里森在另一名男子的陪同下上岸，索要这名青少年的钱包。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;然后，他在一次错误的抢劫中向受害者开了四到五枪。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;科里森不认罪周六被捕的 33 岁男子已被还押，将于周日在帕拉马塔当地法院受审，他被指控犯有谋杀罪和多种武器罪指控。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在搜查 Collision 最后一次出现的房产后逮捕了他。在烧毁的树干中发现了一些据信是人类的骨头。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;警方将在法庭上指控该男子因纠纷在该物业中开枪打死科里森。&lt;/p>;&lt;br >;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/ a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 05 Nov 2023 09:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Russell Brand sexual assault claimant felt ‘used and abused’ on film set]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/nov/04/russell-brand-sexual-assault-claimant-felt-used-and-abused-on-film-set]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T23:39:50Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/026284a419c9a46febebc2da999fc02bf88ea4aa/0_236_4608_2765 /master/4608.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=1a121424d9060b42cff73934eefb024b&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;身穿棕色皮夹克的拉塞尔·布兰德特写&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;自称演员的演员喜剧演员拉塞尔·布兰德 (Russell Brand) 在 2011 年喜剧片《亚瑟》(Arthur) 的拍摄现场对她进行了性侵犯，她说她感觉被他“利用和虐待”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这名未透露姓名的女子在 2011 年提起的诉讼中表示，纽约州周五表示，布兰德首次在《亚瑟》的一些演员和工作人员的众目睽睽之下向她暴露自己，该片是在纽约拍摄的。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;她进一步声称，当天晚些时候，布兰德进入了”当一名制作人员从外面看守门时”，她进入了她所在的厕所，并袭击了她。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我感到被利用和虐待，”她告诉《星期日泰晤士报》。 “恶心是唯一的词。我觉得我被利用了，我只是他短暂兴奋的一个对象。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这位女士声称电影制作中存在严重的权力不平衡，特别是在明星和那些角色较小或角色较小的人之间。额外的。 “每个人通常都会对片场的不良行为视而不见，”她说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“如果我出面对片场的制作助理说些什么，他们会怎么做？去做？他们是要解雇拉塞尔·布兰德，还是要解雇我？”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这起法律案件是在几名女性对这位 48 岁表演者提出一系列指控后指控他性侵犯和布兰德否认了《星期日泰晤士报》、《泰晤士报》和第 4 频道《Dispatches》调查中四名女性的指控，并表示他的恋爱关系始终是双方自愿的。他尚未对纽约诉讼作出回应。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;发行《亚瑟》的华纳兄弟影业公司以及参与电影制作的其他公司也被列为诉讼被告。他们被指控疏忽大意，并通过容忍布兰德在片场的不当行为来帮助和教唆他。一张桌子盯着她，“公开地、明显地当着现场所有人的面”，包括认为他的行为可以接受的电影制片厂员工。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这名女子说，布兰德跟着她进了厕所，在那里他再次脱下他的裤子，然后把她推到隔间里，强迫她为他口交。&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https: //feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color :orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 05 Nov 2023 08:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Hostage situation’ at Hamburg airport as gunman drives on to runway]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/04/hostage-situation-at-hamburg-airport-as-armed-man-drives-on-to-runway]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T23:17:14Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/64b140e42b74e9aa6c371a1dd01b4e82076e576e/0_291_6048_3627 /master/6048.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=3cb64e0ef180c8e069aeb66fee7200fa&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;紧急服务人员赶赴汉堡机场现场。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;德国警方表示，他们正在处理汉堡机场发生“人质事件”，当地媒体报道称，车内有一名武装男子和两名儿童。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“目前警方正在汉堡机场的停机坪上开展大规模行动，”写道周六，汉堡警方在 X（前身为 Twitter）上发布消息。 “我们在现场有大量紧急服务人员。我们目前假设人质劫持情况处于静态。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;机场在其网站上表示，“由于警方行动，目前无法起飞和降落”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;警方发言人称，当地时间晚上 8 点左右，一名枪手将汽车冲过安全区，撞上停机坪，向空中开了两枪，并将两个燃烧的瓶子从车内扔出。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;警方称，车内至少有两人，其中包括一名儿童。发言人补充说，司机的妻子已拨打紧急电话，提醒警方她的孩子被绑架。这辆车仍然停在机场停机坪区域。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;警方周六晚些时候补充说，他们认为“监护权纠纷是这次行动的背景”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;心理学家也是如此警方表示，由于专门负责谈判的官员在现场，并补充说他们正在与车内的人保持联系。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 05 Nov 2023 07:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Albanese arrives in China for landmark visit, says it’s in ‘our national interest’]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/nov/05/anthony-albanese-arrives-for-china-visit-meeting-xi-jinping-and-li-qiang-in-australia-national-interest]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T21:26:24Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7fe1eba235dbaa3dbd98bf871575e45e7b89144d/0_479_8058_4835 /master/8058.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=f0ed77d44fbcd01141bfe2da56cbfaee&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Anthony Albanese 于周六晚抵达中国上海虹桥机场。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/australia-news/anthony-albanese&quot;>;安东尼·阿尔巴内塞&lt;/a>;宣布澳大利亚将“尽我们所能与中国合作，在总理抵达中华人民共和国进行具有里程碑意义的为期三天的正式访问时，我们必须不同意，但……也要参与我们的国家利益。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;阿尔巴内塞于周六晚上抵达上海。在机场受到两国高级外交官的接见后，总理立即前往上海出席中国总理李强为中国国际进口博览会开幕举行的宴会。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;从宴会回来后总理告诉旅行记者，与我们最大的贸易伙伴中国进行积极、建设性、尊重和开放的对话符合澳大利亚的国家利益。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/commentisfree/2023/nov/04/anthony-albanese-china-trip-xi-jinping-meeting-australia-relationship&quot;>;安东尼·阿尔巴内斯会见习近平是中国和澳大利亚之间重建信任的一步——但它能持续下去吗？&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;“这就是我希望在未来几天实现的目标，”总理说。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;阿尔巴尼斯在国内面临一些批评，因为在澳大利亚人面临生活成本压力之际，他仍保持繁忙的国际旅行计划。总理周六晚上指出，中国是澳大利亚最大的贸易伙伴，阿尔巴内斯指出澳大利亚四分之一的工作岗位“依赖于贸易”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;阿尔巴内斯对中国的访问是自 2016 年以来澳大利亚总理的首次访问.他将于周一在北京会见中国国家主席习近平，周二会见总理。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www .theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/nov/04/a-new-chapter-how-china-sees-albaneses-ice-broken-state-visit&quot;>;新篇章：中国如何看待阿尔巴尼斯的“破冰行动” &#39; 国事访问&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;此次访问的目的是在澳大利亚决定将中国公司华为排除在 5G 网络建设之外之后一段时期的重大动荡之后重启外交关系2018年。时任总理斯科特·莫里森呼吁对2020年大流行的起源进行独立调查后，双边裂痕加剧并演变成贸易战。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周日，总理将出席贸易战参观上海世博会，并在澳大利亚旅游局组织的活动中会见澳大利亚和中国商界领袖，然后晚上飞往北京。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Albanese 表示，他打算在这次访问期间提出人权和领事问题。周六，在离开澳大利亚之前，阿尔巴内斯被问到他会对中国总理兼国家主席杨恒均说些什么，杨恒均一直在&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023 /nov/01/yang-hengjuns-australian-writer-jailed-china-family-plea-albanese-negotiate-release&quot;>;被拘留四年。&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/commentisfree/2023/nov/04/can-anthony-albanese-catch-the-dragons-tail-to-defrost -and-reboot-australia-china-relations&quot;>;安东尼·艾博尼斯能否抓住龙尾，解冻并重启澳中关系？ |凯瑟琳·墨菲&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;阿尔巴尼斯说：“我会说杨博士的案子需要解决。我将谈论他的人权、拘留的性质以及透明程序的失败。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“当我们与国际领导人会面时，我们将始终提出澳大利亚公民的问题。这是我们一贯做的事情，我会再次这样做，旨在为杨博士及其家人的利益取得成果。”&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href= “https://feedx.best” style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 05 Nov 2023 05:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Zelenskiy denies he is under pressure to enter peace talks with Russia]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/04/zelenskiy-denies-he-is-under-pressure-to-enter-peace-talks-with-russia]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T16:03:15Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/41b4b721c348d19be1ede54ed48f3c868a100b79/97_194_2790_1673 /master/2790.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=eb1028852c0d8c03a35892a80d1cd9c5&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;欧盟委员会主席乌苏拉·冯德莱恩 (Ursula von der Leyen) 与弗拉基米尔·泽伦斯基 (Volodymyr Zelenskiy) 一起抵达乌克兰基辅举行的新闻发布会。周六。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;乌克兰总统弗拉基米尔·泽连斯基 (Volodymyr Zelenskiy) 否认了西方国家向基辅施压，要求其与俄罗斯进行和平谈判的说法。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;此前，美国全国广播公司 (NBC) 报道了美国和欧洲官员的报道。已与乌克兰政府讨论了与俄罗斯可能进行的和平谈判可能需要采取什么措施来结束战争。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周六，泽连斯基否认乌克兰与俄罗斯的战争已经陷入“僵局”，并反驳了西方领导人的​​说法。游说和平谈判。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“时间已经过去，人们已经疲倦了......但这并不是僵局，”泽伦斯基在基辅与欧盟委员会主席乌苏拉·冯德莱恩一起举行的新闻发布会上表示。&lt; /p>; &lt;p>;“我们的合作伙伴中没有人向我们施压，要求我们与俄罗斯坐下来交谈，并给它一些东西。”&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/nov/04/continued-support-for-ukraine-will-cost-the-west-less-than-letting-putin-win&quot;>;继续支持乌克兰将比让普京获胜让西方付出更少的代价菲利普·英曼&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;本周，乌克兰总司令瓦莱里·扎卢日尼 (Valerii Zaluzhnyi) 告诉《经济学人》：“就像第一次世界大战一样，我们已经达到了使我们陷入了僵局。很可能不会有深刻而漂亮的突破。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但泽连斯基表示，2022年，人们普遍认为乌克兰军队在取得进展之前处于胶着状态。&lt;/p>; &lt;p >;“一些军事伎俩，你记得，哈尔科夫地区就解放了。我们没有权利放弃。还有什么选择呢？什么，我们需要放弃三分之一的州？这只是一个开始。我们知道什么是冻结冲突，我们已经为自己得出了结论。我们需要与防空伙伴进行更多合作，疏通天空，让我们的战斗机有机会进行进攻行动。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;随着战争进入第 20 个月，乌克兰 &lt;a href=&quot;https: //www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/08/as-ukraine-reels-from-attacks-on-land-conflict-at-sea-signals-hope&quot;>;努力取得进展&lt;/a>;泽伦斯基表示，以色列和哈马斯之间的战争也转移了人们对乌克兰的注意力，并表示这是“俄罗斯的目标” ”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“当然，很明显，中东战争，这场冲突，正在分散人们的注意力，”泽连斯基说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们已经陷入了非常严重的境地。” “在几乎没有关注乌克兰的情况下，我们面临着困难的局面，”他说，但他补充道：“我绝对相信我们会克服这一挑战。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;乌克兰的支持者，包括美国，坚称他们已准备好为基辅提供军事和财政支持，只要打败俄罗斯就够了。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;泽伦斯基发表此番言论之际，冯德莱恩访问基辅，讨论乌克兰加入 27 个成员国集团的进展。&lt;/p>; &lt; p>;基辅在去年俄罗斯入侵几个月后获得了欧盟候选资格，但分析人士警告说，它面临着一条漫长而艰难的入盟之路。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“你们已经达到了许多里程碑，”冯德莱恩告诉泽连斯基。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“改革司法系统。遏制寡头的控制。打击洗钱等等，”她说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们永远不应该忘记，你们正在打一场关乎生死存亡的战争，同时你们正在深刻改革你们的国家，”她补充道。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; >; &lt;p>;她表示，当这些改革实施后，她“相信”乌克兰将在入盟进程中取得进展。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;欧盟委员会提议在 2027 年之前为乌克兰额外提供 500 亿欧元（合 540 亿美元）资金”，冯德莱恩说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;几乎所有欧盟成员国都支持对基辅提供进一步的长期援助，只有匈牙利和斯洛伐克坚持不懈。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;委员会现在必须在周三之前提交报告一份关于乌克兰以及其他有望加入欧盟的国家摩尔多瓦和格鲁吉亚在 12 月欧盟峰会之前取得多少进展的报告。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 05 Nov 2023 00:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Storm Ciarán leaves seven dead in Italy as torrential rain causes flooding]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/04/storm-ciaran-italy-deaths-torrential-rain-flooding]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T14:44:01Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c321423c5772ffd8b6a51f8ee76fe1fa9cc3786c/0_87_3072_1844 /master/3072.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=1b0967e359437da9c39f6a81bf65038c&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;佛罗伦萨比森齐奥风暴过后，人们在被洪水淹没的街道上&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;第七个人据安莎通讯社报道，意大利中部托斯卡纳地区暴雨导致河流决堤，一天多后，有人被发现死亡，另一人仍然失踪。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;一具 69 岁老人的尸体该通讯社称，该男子在佛罗伦萨西北约 9 英里（15 公里）的比森齐奥镇被发现。官员早些时候表示，周四晚间开始的洪水已造成六人死亡。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;附近城镇被风暴塞伦南部边缘淹没后，人们担心阿诺河可能会淹没佛罗伦萨，但最高水位周五上午，供水点通过，这座历史名城没有发生重大事件。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/03/tuscany-floods -storm-ciaran-river-flooding&quot;>;塞兰受到从大西洋席卷而来的强大急流的推动&lt;/a>;，带来暴雨和狂风，导致英国、比利时、荷兰和英国部分地区发生严重洪水。法国。安莎社周六援引托斯卡纳地区总统尤金尼奥·贾尼的话说，大约 300 人被迫撤离托斯卡纳的家园，而其他许多人的水和电力供应也被切断。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他补充说，根据初步估计，这场灾难已造成 3 亿欧元（2.6 亿英镑）的损失。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;另一名消防员在威尼托地区东北部失踪， Sky TG24 周五援引了州长的话说。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-atom-id=&quot;4f20a349-36e4-4091-a134-ce3af7b73ceb&quot; data-atom-type=&quot;media&quot;>; &lt;div>; &lt; div style=&quot;font-size:0&quot;>; __YOUTUBE_MEDIA_PLACEHOLDER_4f20a349-36e4-4091-a134-ce3af7b73ceb__ &lt;iframe id=&quot;gu-video-youtube-4f20a349-36e4-4091-a134-ce3af7b73ceb&quot; src=&quot;https://www. youtube-nocookie.com/embed/ay2fchIDjYM?modestbranding=1&amp;amp;showinfo=0&amp;amp;rel=0&amp;amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;amp;embed_config=%7B%22disableAds%22%3Atrue%2C%22nonPersonalizedAd%22%3Atrue%2C%22restrictedDataProcessor%22 %3Atrue%2C%22adsConfig%22%3A%7B%22adTagParameters%22%3A%7B%22cmpGdpr%22%3A1%7D%7D%7D&quot;frameborder=&quot;0&quot;allowfullscreen>;&lt;/iframe>; &lt;/div>; &lt;/ div>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;意大利政府于周五宣布进入紧急状态，并拨款 500 万欧元来帮助受灾最严重的地区。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;意大利多个地区的天气警报仍然有效，在该国遭受强风和大雨袭击一周后，一些学校关闭。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;意大利被认为特别容易受到气候变化的影响。 5 月份艾米利亚-罗马涅地区的洪水造成至少 14 人死亡。&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot; _blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 04 Nov 2023 23:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Toddler in hospital after dumped gun discharges at Las Vegas playground]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/04/toddler-in-hospital-after-dumped-gun-discharges-at-las-vegas-playground]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T12:53:45Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/6e6128244574395e34271616bd87f89f1ecf9457/0_238_7128_4277 /master/7128.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=f57d47e8700d0151b9307580f29249d7&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;据称，一名青少年在城市公交车上开枪打死一名男子后与他人发生争执。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;当局于周五宣布，拉斯维加斯一名幼儿在日托操场上发现一把枪，该枪是一名向城市公交车开火后逃跑的青少年丢弃的，目前情况危急。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;副警察警长雷吉·雷德 (Reggie Rader) 表示，这名 5 岁以下的幼儿“发现了枪支，捡起了枪，然后枪就开火了。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;雷德表示，这名幼儿目前情况稳定，但情况危急。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;雷德表示，这名幼儿目前情况稳定，但情况危急。警方在拉斯维加斯东北部的日托中心地区发现了嫌疑人并将其拘留。 Rader 没有透露嫌疑人的身份，他说嫌疑人还不到 18 岁。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Rader 表示，目前还不清楚这名少年将面临什么指控，但警察局正在与当地地方检察官办公室协商有关事宜。 “所有适用的费用”以及他是否会像成年人一样被收费。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;当局称，这名少年当时正在从城市公交车上跑下来，然后跳过一堵墙，进入日托中心的游乐场区域。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; >; &lt;p>;雷德说，这名少年在公交车上与一名男子发生争执，并掏出枪向他开枪。雷德说，该男子也已入院治疗，目前情况稳定。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 04 Nov 2023 21:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Himmler ordered mass execution of prisoners in Britain’s only Nazi camp, documents reveal]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/04/himmler-execution-prisoners-britain-nazi-concentration-camp]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T13:00:40Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/d783c19daf47a2d5779d2ce7c​​c3fde320592a026/265_221_5192_3117 /master/5192.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=5c2d67bb38660bee3d4a29e6462e87af&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;奥尔德尼集中营俄罗斯囚犯的坟墓。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;海因里希·希姆莱秘密命令《观察家报》此前未公开的文件透露，英国奥尔德尼岛上的 1,000 名奴隶劳工将被冷血枪杀。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;党卫军领导人的直接书面命令这是第一个已知的指示，表明制定计划的目的是消灭英国领土上唯一的纳粹集中营和劳改营的所有居住者。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;希姆莱是大屠杀的关键设计师，他向指挥官们发出指示如果奥尔德尼岛制造麻烦，“立即”谋杀所有囚犯和劳工。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/ aug/13/the-holocaust-happened-on-british-soil-inquiry-into-nazi-camps-creates-bitter-divide-on-alderney&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;纳粹占领&lt;/a>;，海峡群岛，英国皇家属地，设有四个劳工场所，其中包括一个集中营，其中的居住者被迫建造希特勒所谓的大西洋墙的巨大防御工事。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;来自党卫军总部、日期为 1943 年的其他文件表明奥尔德尼岛的囚犯死亡人数可能远多于官方公布的近 400 人死亡人数。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;政府目前正在尝试&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/ 2023/jul/22/nazi-atrocities-jews-prisoners-war-alderney-channel-island-uk&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;通过计算被监禁的囚犯人数来确定&lt;/a>;奥尔德尼岛大屠杀的确切规模由英国大屠杀特使皮克尔斯勋爵领导的持续审查被谋杀。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;尽管公众已经&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gov.uk/guidance/public-submissions-to- support-review-into-the-number-of-prisoners-who-died-on-alderney-during-the-nazi-occupation&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;邀请&lt;/a>;向审查提交证据，对向潜在贡献者发出的“居高临下”指示说服了著名战时历史学家和作家伊恩·塞耶 (Ian Sayer) 将其档案中的党卫军文件交给了&lt;em>;观察家&lt;/em>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id= &quot;d468dc93cffe6ab7fb1a49ee975609972f7aea14&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/d468dc93cffe6ab7fb1a49ee975609972f7aea14/1754_804_5726_3438/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;营地的大门。” width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;营地门口的牌匾。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：Carl Court/Getty Images&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/图>; &lt;p>;这些文件中有一封希姆莱写给奥尔德尼岛党卫军建筑旅指挥官马克西米利安·李斯特的信。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;日期为 1943 年 8 月 19 日，标记为绝密希姆莱的信中写道：“一旦发生袭击，如果囚犯有哪怕是最轻微的迹象表明他们打算制造麻烦，你必须立即采取行动，不拘礼节，射杀罪犯。&lt; /p>; &lt;p>;“如果秩序仍未恢复，你们必须立即射杀所有囚犯。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这封信是由信使亲手交给李斯特的，并附有希姆莱的具体命令以确保他谋杀数百名手无寸铁且受虐待的奴隶劳工的指示永远不会被公开。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“他[List]将其阅读三遍以上，然后通过您自己再次发回给我，而无需希姆莱说，他对第三帝国的许多最严重的罪行负有责任。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;教授 &lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis .com/international/lists/tag/profile/richard-j-evans&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;理查德·埃文斯&lt;/a>;，剑桥大学历史学名誉教授，认为希姆莱的命令可能是由于特雷布林卡囚犯起义，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/feb/20/samuel-willenberg-survivor-of-nazi-death-camp-treblinka-dies-ged -93&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;被占领的波兰境内最致命的&lt;/a>;纳粹灭绝营，发生在党卫军头子写信给李斯特的几天前。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“特雷布林卡于 2 日发生了囚犯起义。 1943 年 8 月，希姆莱可能对此感到担忧。也许也是因为五月份的华沙隔都起义。这种反应对希姆莱来说是相当标准的。”埃文斯说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;然而，德国历史国际专家埃文斯表示，直到八月下旬，才能完全确定党卫军头目是否被告知特雷布林卡起义。&lt; /p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;74a2987111424ce7f5c8ac1692d682cebf94d368&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/74a2987111424ce7f5c8ac1692d682cebf94d368/0_567_2955_1773/1 000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;海因里希·希姆莱。&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;海因里希·希姆莱是大屠杀的建筑师之一。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：Bettmann/Bettmann Archive&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt; /figure>; &lt;p>;根据之前未公开的文件，更确定的是希姆莱在英国领土上杀害囚犯的命令试图保密。 1943 年 9 月 15 日的另一封信透露，另一名党卫军军官 - &lt;em>;Obergruppenführer&lt;/em>; Oswald Pohl - 通知希姆莱的副官鲁道夫·勃兰特，所有与奥尔德尼岛杀戮命令有关的文件都已被销毁。&lt;/em>; p>; &lt;p>;“关于这个主题的任何书面材料已经不存在了”，这封信也被标记为绝密。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;然而希姆莱的信以某种方式幸存下来，并且很可能是从党卫军总部被洗劫一空。战后，于 1983 年 6 月在纽约拍卖会上被 Sayer 收购。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com /uk-news/2023/aug/13/the-holocaust-happened-on-british-soil-inquiry-into-nazi-camps-creates-bitter-divide-on-alderney&quot;>;“大屠杀发生在英国土地上” ：对纳粹集中营的调查在奥尔德尼岛造成了严重分歧&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;这位 78 岁的老人因追踪被盗的纳粹黄金和战犯以及领导权威而闻名核实战时文件，但对将其提供给&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gov.uk/government/news/review-into-the-number-of-prisoners-who-died-on 感到不舒服-alderney-during-the-nazi-occupation&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;政府的审查&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“作为多年来协助各种社团、博物馆、作家和记者的人， by providing copies of documents, and letters from my second world war archive, I thought I could make a contribution,” said Sayer, who in 1988 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.andrewlownie.co.uk/authors/ian -sayer&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;tracked down&lt;/a>; the world&#39;s most senior surviving Nazi, SS General Wilhelm Mohnke.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Sayer believes the government&#39;s instructions for public submissions will deter members of the public wanting to help , particularly the threat from the inquiry that documents not supplied in a certain format “will be &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gov.uk/guidance/public-submissions-to-support-review-into-the-number -of-prisoners-who-died-on-alderney-during-the-nazi-occupation&quot; title=&quot;&quot;>;disregarded&lt;/a>;”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Describing the SS documents as of “considerable historical significance ” Sayer added: “The inquiry itself is a worthy cause but it is not right to treat people you are asking for help in this way.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Professor &lt;a href=&quot;https://committees.parliament .uk/writtenevidence/61020/html/&quot;>;Robert Jan Van Pelt &lt;/a>;of Canada&#39;s University of Waterloo, a leading expert on Auschwitz, corroborated the authenticity of the documents, concluding they were “undoubtedly genuine.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Pelt, who was an expert witness in the London trial of Holocaust-denier &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2017/jan/15/david-irving-youtube-inspiring -holocaust-deniers&quot;>;David Irving&lt;/a>; is also currently on the expert panel of the Alderney inquiry led by Pickles.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The same set of documents collected by Sayer reveal insights into the SS construction brigade charged with building up the Nazi&#39;s defences on Alderney, with one passage applauding the work ethic of the enslaved labourers, saying “the prisoners&#39; productivity equalled that of German workers”.&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot; https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 04 Nov 2023 21:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[UK urges Iran to use influence to avert escalation in Israel-Hamas conflict]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/04/uk-urges-iran-influence-escalation-israel-hamas-conflict-gaza]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T11:43:04Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/861c3fc135b30a9b9ac1e8b5355f490fff420e18/832_94_1461_877/master/1461.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=14cb482315c75a2a9254042d595dcccc&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;James Cleverly walking in Downing Street&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;The UK foreign secretary, James Cleverly, in a rare phone call with his Iranian counterpart, has underlined western warnings that Tehran must use its influence with other groups in the Middle East to prevent escalation in the Gaza conflict.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;It is not clear from the readouts given by either side whether Cleverly spelled out any consequences to Iran if it was deemed to be actively stoking a wider war, or if he provided any intelligence to show that the west knew the depth of Iran&#39;s involvement.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Iranian foreign minister, Hossein Amir-Abdollahian, rejected Cleverly&#39;s message by repeating the longstanding line that Iran does not control militant groups in the Palestinian territories, Lebanon, Iraq, Syria or Yemen, also known as the “axis of resistance”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In a longer readout of the call than the brief summary provided by the UK Foreign Office, the Iranian foreign ministry said Cleverly was urged to adopt a realistic approach to the conflict and recognise that the “resistance forces” were fighting an occupation by an Israeli government that was committing war crimes amounting to genocide and acting without any proportionaliity.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/04/gaza-ceasefire-talks-ongoing-despite-israeli-pm-rejecting-pause-says-us&quot;>;Gaza ceasefire talks ongoing despite Israeli PM rejecting &#39;pause&#39;, says US&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;Amir-Abdollahian said international law gave people of an occupied country a legitimate right to defend themselves.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“In that vein, he noted, the massacre of more than 9,000 Palestinian civilians, in an act of revenge and genocide openly declared by the Zionist regime, is not acceptable by any metric,” the Iranian foreign ministry reported.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Amir-Abdollahian said the extensive support provided by the US government to Tel Aviv was responsible for the escalation of the war in the region.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The leader of Hezbollah in Lebanon, Hassan Nasrallah, claimed &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/nov/03/hezbollah-leader-threatens-escalation-in-fighting-with-israel&quot;>;in a speech&lt;/a>; on Friday the group was warned through US intermediaries that the US would attack Iran if Hezbollah joined the war against Israel.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Nasrallah&#39;s speech suggested that the threat of a full-blown immediate escalation had receded, but the possibility of a slow escalation remains in what is a highly volatile environment.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Attacks on US bases in Iraq are likely to increase, but Hamas would most like to see Hezbollah tie down Israeli forces by opening up a full second front on the boundary between south Lebanon and Israel. Hezbollah has already lost 50 fighters.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Some Iranian officials believe that the long-term damage being done to the US and Israel&#39;s international standing is so great that they do not need at this stage to try to tip the military balance.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In his call, Cleverly also said &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/oct/30/british-counter-terror-officers-closely-monitoring-iran-amid-heightened-risk&quot;>;Iranian-backed threats against people in the UK &lt;/a>;were unacceptable and must stop. The British intelligence services have said there have been as many as 15 credible threats to the lives of people in the UK.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Iran&#39;s supreme leader, Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, earlier this week scoffed at suggestions that the country&#39;s Basij volunteer paramilitary force were organising pro-Palestinian demonstrations in London and Paris.&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 04 Nov 2023 20:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Model says her face was edited with AI to look white: ‘It’s very dehumanizing’]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/nov/04/fashion-model-ai-image-tiktok]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-11-04T11:00:39Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/f26e77006ce1b4accaab8ef8c7fff76c664663c3/0_0_3000_1800/master/3000.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=ba2a91d40fe0924881737b8fdcbc1259&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;side by side images from tiktok showing wu and a digitally altered image of a white woman&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;A Taiwanese American model says a well-known fashion designer uploaded a digitally altered runway photo that made her appear white.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.tiktok.com/@shereenwu/video/7295068175526481198&quot;>;TikTok&lt;/a>; about the incident that has been viewed 1.8m times in the last week, Shereen Wu says Michael Costello, a designer who has worked with Beyoncé, Jennifer Lopez, and Celine Dion, posted a photo to his Instagram from a recent Los Angeles fashion show. The photo depicts Wu in the slinky black ballgown that she walked the runway in –&amp;nbsp;but her face has been changed, made to appear as if she is a white woman.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In a statement posted to Instagram on Thursday and deleted less than 24 hours later, Costello denied altering the photo and said the image was “fan art” sent to him by an unspecified source, but he “took responsibility” for sharing it. “I didn&#39;t think before resharing it on my Instagram Stories as I was on an emotional rollercoaster, resharing all that I was tagged in,” the statement read. (Costello did not respond to a request for comment.)&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;As a 21-year-old independent model who is not signed to an agency, Wu relies on small jobs to continue working. She said she did not get paid for the show, which took place during Art Hearts, a Los Angeles fashion week.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;To Wu, that&#39;s not an issue, as long as it gets her face out there. “I expected to be paid in exposure,” she said. “But I didn&#39;t get exposure, because this is an edited photo. By cutting off my head, neither did the makeup&lt;strong>; &lt;/strong>;artist, hairdresser or photographer. That&#39;s what peeves me so much.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Wu added that her mother was the first person to notice that her face had been replaced. “My initial reaction was, &#39;Who would remove someone&#39;s head like that?&#39;” Wu said. “My next reaction was fear, then a sense of melancholy because my mom had to see her daughter&#39;s face cut.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In his now deleted Instagram post, Costello said that “in light of the false allegations presented in [Wu&#39;s] videos”, his eponymous brand is “moving forward with legal proceedings”. His statement does contradict smaller points in Wu&#39;s story, such as the fact that she was a replacement for another model in the runway show. According to his post, he did not produce the show and did not know that Wu was not compensated for her time until he saw her TikTok. “After finding out through her videos that she wasn&#39;t paid, I offered Shereen compensation for her time and talents,” Costello wrote. He also said he was receiving death threats and that the show was a tribute to his aunt, who recently passed away.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Erik Rosete, a fashion designer and president of Art Hearts, said the organization could not afford to pay all the models it takes to put on shows for over 30 designers. “We&#39;re all doing this for exposure, and to take that away from anybody is taking away their time and their dignity,” he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-canonical-url=&quot;https://www.tiktok.com/@shereenwu/video/7295068175526481198&quot;>; &lt;iframe height=&quot;700&quot; width=&quot;340&quot; src=&quot;https://www.tiktok.com/embed/v2/7295068175526481198&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; allowfullscreen>;&lt;/iframe>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;While the origin of the altered runway photo is unknown, Wu believes someone – she doesn&#39;t know who – used AI to create the white face that covered hers, a theory Costello echoed in his Instagram post.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Ten years ago, models complained about their bodies being photoshopped to an emaciated degree. In 2009, for example, Filippa Hamilton &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.smh.com.au/lifestyle/model-in-altered-ralph-lauren-ad-speaks-out-20091015-gy25.html&quot;>;spoke out&lt;/a>; when the Ralph Lauren brand altered her image, slimming her hips to the size of her head. Now, the fashion world faces issues of how to ethically use AI, a technology that has been &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/interactive/2023/ai-generated-images-bias-racism-sexism-stereotypes/&quot;>;shown&lt;/a>; to bake racist and sexist stereotypes into the imagery it creates.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Earlier this year, Levi&#39;s announced that it would use computer-generated models on its website in an effort to include a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/apr/03/ai-virtual-models-fashion-brands?utm_term=Autofeed&amp;amp;CMP=twt_gu&amp;amp;utm_medium&amp;amp;utm_source=Twitter#Echobox=1680522321&quot;>;diverse range&lt;/a>; of ethnicities. Critics of the decision said that if brands truly wished to enrich people of color, they should hire human models.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;For Susan Scafidi, academic director of Fordham&#39;s Fashion Law Institute, changing a real model&#39;s ethnicity with AI is another part of this evolution.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“The modified image of Shereen spotlights the possibility that an AI program that has absorbed mainstream beauty preferences may erase the race of a model altogether, turning back the clock on the fashion industry&#39;s progress toward diversity on the runway,” Scafidi said. She said Wu and other models had little recourse in these situations: copyright law protects photographers whose work is altered without permission, but it does not extend to the models they shoot.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Wu said: “I hope people can understand how hurtful it is to have your work stolen from you. It&#39;s very dehumanizing. The very thing that makes us human is our ability to create something beautiful, and to have this beauty be twisted into something that can potentially be ugly is a terrifying thought.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;As Sinead Bovell, a model and tech commentator who &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vogue.com/article/sinead-bovell-model-artificial-intelligence&quot;>;wrote&lt;/a>; about the ethics of AI models for Vogue in 2020, put it: “[Wu] was erased from the digital world, which matters because the digital world is a real place for models. It leads to real economic and visible pathways.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;This is not the first controversy attached to Costello&#39;s name. In 2021, Chrissy Teigen, the model and cookbook author, faced allegations of bullying. As the Cut reported, Costello added to the pile-on, sharing screenshots via Instagram of a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.thecut.com/2021/06/the-michael-costello-bullying-controversy-explained.html&quot;>;supposed&lt;/a>; DM conversation with Teigen that left him “traumatized, depressed” with “thoughts of suicide”. But after he posted, others accused Costello of sexual harassment, racism and body shaming, and Teigen said that the screenshots had been altered, statements Costello described as false.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;After Costello&#39;s threat of legal action over her viral Tiktok, Wu contacted the Model Alliance, an advocacy group for fashion workers, which referred her to a lawyer.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“For over a decade, we&#39;ve heard from models who have walked into a store or browsed a company&#39;s website only to find that their image has been heavily manipulated or otherwise used without their informed consent or compensation,” Sara Ziff, founder of the Model Alliance, said. “Unfortunately, Shereen&#39;s experience is one of the many examples of why models need protections as workers.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Ultimately, as Ziff said, “AI technology may be new, but the problem of models&#39; images being misused is not.”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 04 Nov 2023 19:52:02 +0800</pubDate></item></channel></rss>